HEADWORD: Six-shooter
<hw>Six"-shoot`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A pistol or
other firearm which can be fired six times without reloading especially,
a six-chambered revolver.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

